The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Brazil lose No. 1 status to Italy

Zurich: World Cup holders Italy have knocked Brazil off the top of Fifas world rankings after four and a half years. 

Brazil, who won the 2002 World Cup but were eliminated by France in last years quarter finals, lost top spot after a 0-2 friendly defeat at the hands of Portugal last week, Fifa said on Wednesday. 

The six teams below Italy and Brazil remain unchanged, with Argentina, France, Germany, England, The Netherlands and Portugal occupying the third to eighth spots. 

India, meanwhile, remain at No. 157. (Reuters) 




